column5: Heading out right now. 32" of ice and -2 at the moment. Hoping to put some fish on the ice today! Thanks Terry for the words of advice on the graph last night! Im sure it'll help alot today;) pics shortly(i hope) hahaha. Have a safe day on the ice people!!!!

Man brutal. 12 of us fishing, only two good fish caught(25" and a 26.5" walleye). Nothing noteworthy at all on the fish side of things  missed alot of bites, drilled what had to be 300 holes in all, just wasnt our day. On the plus side, met some new friends, had GREAT weather, kiddos had a blast snowboarding near the river and we had a beauty sun out there:) terry, your setting were bang on!!!! Thanks dood, those minor changes made a hyyyuge difference! Lots of fishing for me coming up, so im just gonna do reports in this thread as apposed to starting new ones. Have a few nights on the ice this week then LOTW next weekend!!!!! Stay thiraty my friends;)
nothing noteworthy? I'd say a 25 and 26.5" walleye are noteworthy!
I would love to have a camera down the hole watching
No fish pics, but nature was a beauty today:)
